      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Patient's Suicide</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Dr. Elissa Ely's thoughtful commentary on exploring her former patient's MySpace site after his suicide (Cases, April 17) is marred by her observation that the messages there ''were not written to a haunted self, or someone who had failed trials of antipsychotic drugs.'' Those suffering from brain illnesses have enough burdens without being labeled failures. It was surely the antipsychotic drugs that failed, not the patient.</p>
        <p>Suzanne M. Parson  St. Ignatius, Mont.</p>
      </block>
